<scenario>
The agent A provided the following violation scenario:
The for loop's third clause uses the variable 'ret' (off += (size_t) ret), but 'ret' is modified inside the loop body (ret = send(...); ret = 0;). MISRA C 2023 Rule 14.2 clause 3 requires the third clause to modify only the loop counter and not use objects that are modified in the loop body. Because the loop body changes 'ret', the third clause depends on an object modified in the body — this violates Rule 14.2.
</scenario>

